docker image contains of code ,binaries & libraries,dependencies that required to run an app.
  docker container means when an image is successfully pulled and comes into running state 
  then it is considered to be a container by docker 
  commands : docker pull imagename
    docker push imagename
    docker ps -a
    docker ps
    docker images
    docker run imagename
    docker -d -p portnumber imagename
    docker container ls
    docker rm containername
    docker stop containername
    when i have changed port number the port mapping comes into picture and activates the particular
    port number that i have mentioned to the server 
